Alphonso’s Pizzeria is a medium-sized pizza and Italian eatery. very casual dine-in as well as takeout.  decent-sized space with plenty of tables. Alphonso’s also delivers.  can’t speak to the pizza—never had it. i have had the Sausage & Peppers on a hero roll. it was solidly good: grilled onions and peppers, the right amount of sauce, and sliced sausage on a soft long roll. wish there was more sausage on it, so it was an overstuffed sando. however no complaints otherwise.very shareable. ~$10  the fries are the real winner here. crispy outside and soft potato insides. the fries have that double-fried/batter crunch. only $3.50 for a hefty portion.  delivery is fast if you’re in the area aka  Lower East Side.  drops mic cuz food is life

They make a excellent pizza. Customer service is great.  I still like the product they produce. Sorry to say that at the moment their food grade has been removed and they now have a "grade pending". My last two visits were not pleasant. One time I'm eating my pizza and all I hear from the employees is ghetto talking with plenty of profanity. The following viisit the cashier has no etiquette whatsoever. I am disabled and no attempt was made to accommodate me. Perhaps all they care is to sell pizza. I enjoy the food but I hope they can brush on the other things I posted. Best of luck.  They recently got their "A" grade back. I'm happy about that. The food is fresh and tasty. Good luck in maintaining your Grade.

I used to order from this place all the time. Almost weekly. They know me. Tonight I call to place an order and someone new on the phone tells me that they are back up with deliveries so they are not taking any. This person told me they have 7 orders and only 2 delivery people so they could not take any more orders at the moment. I asked when they could. She said she didn’t know. I explained I’m a regular and she said she didn’t care. I then asked if I should just take my business elsewhere moving forward and she hung up the phone. If you have new staff and they can’t handle 7 orders with 2 delivery people in nyc, sounds like you need new staff. Also be professional and not sound clueless.  EDIT: To response below.  I never was told that information about delivery men getting hurt. Also, I never called again about a salad dressing later. I never called again after the hang up or placed an order from my phone (please check your phone records). This just shows dishonesty because none of that is factual. Also, why are you listening in to your employees phone calls when you are too busy to take orders? That does not make sense as well.

Spectacular dinner experience with an enormous amount of care and detail in every single dish served, including the plates and cutlery. We had an 8 course tasting menu which takes you through a mix of unique sea and land ingredients from both Italy and Canada, all carefully cooked and presented. Everything was special from start to finish but the dishes that stood out more for me were the eel gelato, bison filet, triglia with scarola, and final course of dessert with asparagus-white chocolate, raspberry, and hazelnut semifreddo. Atmosphere and service of Michelin Star level to match the incredible food. Bravissimo guagliò!

If you happen to be in the Lower East Side area buying food at the upcoming Trader Joes, and looking for cheap $.99 pizza, don't bother going to Alphonso. I actually came into here looking for some cheap pizza a few weeks ago to hold over my kids hunger. Bad mistake, I have since been coming back regularly for regular slices, vegetable slices, pepperoni slices, pasta specials (meatball and spaghetti, and baked zitti.  I've noticed that the ingredients in the $.99 pizza are totally different.  After eating the $.99 stuff, I am tired, groggy, foggy. With Alphonso stuff, I am more energetic. Best of all my kids like them also. My kIds do not like the spicy pepperoni, they like regular peperoni. The kids also like to have paramsean cheese sprinkled on their pizza. The chef usually put some real parmasean cheese on the slices when asked.  They had a specially made Prosciutto topped pizza that was out of this world. I wished I took a picture of it. Yes, I like Prosciutto. Apparently, it's only made every once in a while.
